      <section eId="sec_CHC-1446">
        <num>CHC 1446</num>
        <heading>1446. Â Record; transcription</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1446__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The court shall cause a recording of the testimony of the hearing to be made, which shall be transcribed only in the event of an appeal from the judgment.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1446__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A copy of such transcript shall be furnished without charge, to any appellant whom the court finds unable to pay for the same.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-1446__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The cost of such transcript shall be paid from funds appropriated to the judicial department.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=72942</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
